section.index
  .jumbotron
    .container
      header.row
        .col-sm-12
          h1 Step into the Film

      .row
        .col-md-8
          :markdown
            **[360 Screenings](http://360screenings.com)** provides a cinematic experience that audiences not only watch, but also become a part of through live theatre installations. The location, a *Toronto* heritage building, is kept secret until 24 hours prior to the screening. You, the audience, are encouraged to explore, uncover and interact with everything that surrounds you. Part film, part theatre, with a dash of mystery.

            Join us **February 7th and 8th** for the next 360 Screenings event: **[LOVE](/2014-02)**. Tickets now on sale!

          p
            a.unii-listing-button.unii-medium.unii-pink(href="https://www.uniiverse.com/listings/360-screenings-love-toronto-B6WFR", target="_blank") Book it!

        .col-md-4
          iframe(height="280", src="//www.youtube.com/embed/D-LHGYeg-yc?rel=0&theme=dark&height=280&modestbranding=1&wmode=transparent", allowfullscreen, title="360 Screenings Recap")

          form.validate.form-inline#mc-embedded-subscribe-form(action="http://360screenings.us5.list-manage2.com/subscribe/post?u=ebc87bb944ba1f4df138fa027&amp;id=144e89fef7", method="post", name="mc-embedded-subscribe-form", _lpchecked="1", role="form")
            .form-group
              label(for="email") Register through email
              input.input-sm.form-control#mce-EMAIL.email(type="email", name="EMAIL", placeholder="Register email address", required="", it="email")
            button#mc-embedded-subscribe.btn.btn-primary.btn-sm(type="submit", value="Subscribe", name="subscribe") Subscribe

  .container
    .row
      ul.eventlisting
        each event in getCollection("events").toJSON()
          li.col-sm-6.col-md-4
            a(href="#{event.url}").thumbnail
              img(src!=getThumbnail(event.thumbnail, "zoomcrop", {w: 400, h: 300}), alt="#{event.title}", title="#{event.title}", width="400", height="300")
              .caption
                h2= event.title
